      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a pot and mix until the cheese is coated in the flour</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>to the pot with your <strong>ground paprika </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 2-3 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>nacho cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
